<!doctype html>
<!--
  adopter-welcome.step-3.mjml — Week 3: team up for greater impact.
  Source: Drip Emails for adopter Sign-up.docx (Email 4).
-->
<html><body style="font-family: sans-serif; max-width: 640px; margin: 0 auto; color: #1f2937;">
  <h2 style="color: #1f2937;">Team Up for Greater Impact</h2>
  <p>Hi {{ contact_display_name }},</p>

  <p>
    Frontier People Group Adoption is sustained through shared ownership.
    The farther removed you are from the culture and location of the people,
    the more you will need to partner with mission organizations and networks
    that will facilitate engagement. "From him the whole body, joined and
    held together by every supporting ligament, grows and builds itself up
    in love, as each part does its work." (Ephesians 4:16 NIV)
  </p>
  <p>
    Partnering with others helps to catalyze the work and allows the impact
    to increase. If you agreed to collaborate with others in FPG adoption,
    Joshua Project will be matching you with an organization working to reach
    your adopted FPG. In many cases there will be no group currently working
    among the FPG to match you with. So, in some cases you will be matched
    with other adopters of the same group. These matches are just one key way
    for you to "team up."
  </p>

  <p>Consider a few other intentional ways teaming up may be possible for you and your group:</p>

  <ol>
    <li>
      <strong>ALIGN WITH VARIOUS PARTNERS.</strong>
      Seek out and connect with individuals, humanitarian organizations,
      churches, movements, or networks to help engage the FPG(s). Partnering
      happens at different levels. You may find that you can partner with
      different groups for different purposes — information exchange, access
      partnership, ministry partnership, evangelism, or core partnership. The
      more extensive the partnership, the greater alignment is needed to work
      together.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>BUILD RELATIONAL TRUST.</strong>
      Get to know other workers and their efforts. Pray with and for these
      workers. Healthy adoption is relational, not transactional.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>SHARE INFORMATION REGULARLY.</strong>
      Updates, prayer requests, and stories keep the partnership alive and
      partners encouraged.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>HELP TO MULTIPLY THE EFFORTS OF OTHERS — AND SHARE UPDATES WITH JOSHUA PROJECT.</strong>
      The information gathered by those who have adopted and are working to
      engage various FPGs is critical to the greater effort. By updating
      Joshua Project, you help to inform and better focus future work
      worldwide.
    </li>
  </ol>

  <p>You were never meant to carry this mission by yourself. Let's increase the impact together.</p>

  <p>With gratitude,<br/>The Joshua Project Team</p>

  <p style="color: #9ca3af; font-size: 12px; margin-top: 32px;">
    Reply "unsubscribe" to stop receiving this series.
  </p>
</body></html>
